<br>
We can already see what would happen by looking at the Status and AoW rotation.  AoW guilds often wait 24 hours for the Statue guild to get over to Kael and kill him.  Which is fine, AoW is one mob, 1-2 hour raid at most.  But NToV is a 10-12 hour raid, over 1 or 2 days.  And it takes a large amount of people.  So NToV guilds really dont want to wait 3 hours for United Necros (used for a generic guild name) kills 2 dragons.<br>
<br>
These 2 mobs need to be killed to get into NToV.  Yes, in theory one could get to Roy without them being dead, but one wrong step by ANYONE in the raid would mean a wipe out and coffin CR.<br>
<br>
FFA on the mobs might work.  And I would be willing to discuss that possibility when another guild has killed them.  But until then you dont really know what it takes to get in to them.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> As I understand the RTA rotations were made to protect the little guilds and I am curious here<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Incorrect.  Rotations were started so the &quot;big&quot; guilds could share mobs.  As other guilds kill we let them onto the rotation.  They are not here to protect smaller guilds, however it is a nice side benefit.<br>
<br>
Rotations and the RTA in general are compromises.  Sometimes the big guild give up something, some times the little guild give up something.  BotS agrees to only kill Trak once in 3 months, even though they can kill him with an exp group... Clan Bashemded agrees to leave not kill Ikky and Eashan. <p><P><A HREF="http://www.jakefitch.com/asb/char_detail.asp?Name=Milambus" TARGET="_blank"><IMG SRC="http://jakefitch.com/sig/eq/sig1.jpg" HEIGHT="150" WIDTH="400" ALT="Milambus Mandragon" BORDER="0"></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugranitfist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Granitfist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/16/02 10:38:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=123.topic&index=39>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ToVN Rotation agreement/rules</span><hr size=1> Thank you for being cool Milabus and I totally agree about the rotation of them.  I didnt see a problem with FCFS on them though, how are people going to see what is up with them if they are never allowed to try?  But its up to you all, I have to go and do a CR heh. <p><center><BR><font color= Blue><BR><i>Granitfist/Jeribu<i/><BR><i>GrandMaster/High Priest<i/><BR><i>Co-Leader of Circles End<i/><BR><i>The Rathe<BR><center><i><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370733">The Monk </> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370756">The Cleric<i/>
